"I don't want anything else in life," she says, before letting her put a breathing mask.
She is still waiting in the coming days of the last visit of her son, who came from Italy.
In the shelter of Victor-Gadbua with the help of a group of volunteers provide body care and nutritional assistance.
This is the palliative care that remains when nothing can be done.
To make death more comfortable.
In Quebec, every 11,700 inhabitants account for one place in palliative care institutions.
This is very little, given that sooner or later we will all die.
Here life continues in the best conditions, which are possible, explains Dr. Christian Martel - one of the doctors of the shelter.
Whether it's physical, emotional or soul comfort.
Dies we will agree to provide mouth stripes from brandy or peps, looking for it to ask.
Diabetes are no longer compelled to control the sugar level.
